This paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it introduces a novel approach to optimization with orthogonal and unitary constraints in neural networks. It also discusses how this approach can be applied to RNNs, which are commonly used in machine learning tasks. Additionally, the paper may also be relevant to the neural networks (cs.NE), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and systems and control (cs.SY) sub-categories as these fields often involve optimization and parameterization techniques.
